Low level: no garanty your boat coming in a good shape after passing Infiernito.

High level: extra caution is required in Infernito

To check the water level go to Malecon area (where most of rafting companies are) and ask them. You can also call to Exploradores Colombia. +57 304 670 0025 (what''s app)

**The run**

After few kilometers from the put in brigde you will find an exciting and good warm up rapids (grade III and III+). As soon as you just finished the rapids, either side you must go and catch an eddy before the Infernito. You will be able to see most of the first part of this steep section. Then there is a big eddy betweenthe upper and the lower section of Infernito. For addicting paddlers take out on the left once you finished and make couple more laps. 

In case of high slows I suggest take the entrace at the left side or in the middle, once get in this puzzle rapid, keep in middle and pray.

Then class 3 comercial section follows and after 10 km finally you get to San Gil where a f*cking cool beer is waitting for you.

**Access**

In San Gil you can get a public bus(located in PUENTE GRANDE, next to the La Hoja de Tabaco and go as far as you want. The ticket is 5000 pesos. You can also go to the Malecon, the area where most of the rafting companies are and ask them for a shuttle.

_Ariel Muoz Delgado, 2017._ [Exploradores Colombia](http://exploradorescolombia.com/)', 'whole year except really dry periods', '', '2018-03-24 15:12:49.178143+00', '2018-03-24 15:12:49.178143+00');

The river is incredibly powerfull and big. BIG. You can serf and boof not only numerous gigantic waves but even turbulences and whirlpools :) It''s very likely that it''s the biggest river you have ever paddled.

There are not that many rapids though and they are fairly easy. Everything can be done without scouting. But don''t hurry up! The scenary is breathtaking. The section starts in the open valley with absolutely flat river. After first hour of paddling the banks become steeper and the current faster. There is not much vegetaion in the valley - on the contrary to [Samana](/rivers/95PjdgnnaxZLoEAe7) which is not that far and at the same altitude.

The further you paddle the steeper and more spectacular the banks become.

**The access**

The _put in_ is next to the historical city called Santa Fe de Antioquia. It''s worth a visit!

If you want to avoid the first kilometers of flat water you can drive the road down on the right side of the river.

The _take out_ is in the area that was recently controlled by guerillas and it''s considered as a dangerous zone. The situation is changing very fast so be sure to ask locals before you commit to this run.

Both roads to the put in and take out are in perfect conditions but it still takes a very long time to shuttle.

**_Note:_** The river is very dirty. There are a lot of cities and plants upstream. Try not to swallow the water.

_Mike Krutyansky, 2017_', 'All year around', '', '2018-03-24 15:12:49.186049+00', '2018-03-24 15:12:49.186049+00');

