**About the river**

Louredo is a special river. It''s born at a big plateau so it stays with water for a long time after rain. It has 4-5 stars whitewater from 900 meters above sea level all the way to the confluence with Tamega at 150 meters just except a big portage between the Genesis and the Upper sections. It''s a must visit river for any class IV-V kayaker. It will be dammed soon.

**Water**

Upper Louredo is possible to paddle 3-7 days after a heavy rain. For the medium level the trees at the put in on the left bank between the weir and the bridge should be around 10 sm out of the water. 4-6 cumecs is a good level. With more water the rapids become better but the pools are too small. When the [Lower Louredo](/sections/j8kq5kuMK2nbyuNhb/) is a bit too low to be perfect it''s a good time to run Upper.

**The run**

The section starts with some flat water but steep and blocked rapids will follow soon. There are some tricky lines, holes and narrow passages. So be ready to scout a lot. The more you paddle the steeper river becomes. The crux part is a combination of a double drop followed by a good pool and then 6 meters cleen drop and a big slide after another short pool. The pool after the slide flows quite fast to the following class VI waterfall. This waterfall has been run successfully but normally it''s a portage. The pool of this waterfall is blocked by a river-wide syphon.

After the portage of this syphon there are few nice rapids and then another nasty rapid without clean lines. Portage or pin. The rest of the run is fair but not very clean. There are numerous artificial high and bony weirs until you reach the take out.

This section will take you a lot of time and energy but if you still want to paddle go on and do the [Lower](/sections/j8kq5kuMK2nbyuNhb/) - easier, cleaner and no portages (if the water level is not too low).

_Note:_ Following the dirt road to the put in just around 1 kilometer before the put in you will see a water channel on the right from the road. If you follow this water channel with boats you will arrive to a nice addition for the run - a class V long and technical rapid.

