The gorge is virtualy inescapable with exception of couple places where you can possibly do a long hike out.

At medium water level there are actually not that many class V rapids but it makes sense to rate the entire multiday run as class V. Also the last day of paddling is not really 5 stars but the whole run is definitely 5 stars.

**The run**

The gradient starts almost immediately. On the first kilometers you will enjoy continious technical steep and already quite demanding boof paradise with enough eddies... if you are lucky with the water level. Class IV+ to V-.

After about 2 hours of paddling from the put in the style of the river changes. It enters very high canyon with sometimes absolutely steep walls. But don''t be scared. All harder rapids are easy to scout and to portage. Suddenly some sweet bedrock rapids appear. At some point there is a huge boulder blocking the entrace to the canyoun with an overhanging right wall. Almost all the river flows under this boulder - portage.

The river gets more and more spectacular with sometimes absolutel red rocks.

After the canyon opens up there will be some flat water to paddle and signes of civilization on the river banks. There is a possibility here for an emergency exit.

Then some rapids begin. The quality of these rapids are much lower than the rapids in the first canyons. They are formed by landslides.

Then the river enters the second big canyon - as spectacular as the first one but with completely different character. The rapids are made of house-size boulders and many of them are sifons. Paddle with caution because soon you will reach an unpaddleable section. Portage left or right takes around 1 hour.

After the portage the river slowly flatterns. You enjoy class III-IV paddling in a breathtaking scenary with waterfalls comming from both sides of the canyon. From the portage it''s around 2 hours to the suspension bridge. It is an option for the take out if your car can drive there. If not you can paddle to the confluence with rio Cubugon and then carry your boats for around 600 meters upstream on the right bank. There you will find a small gravel road passable with a normal car that comes to the river bank.

