**Water**

The river is dammed and it''s very hard to find a proper flow to run this section. There is no online gauge on this river but you can check [percipitation accumulated in Salas](http://saih.chminosil.es/index.php?url=/datos/ficha/estacion:E036/area:HID) artificial lake in last 1 hour, 12 hours and 24 hours. Roughly it should be 30 mm in last 24 hours or more. Salas is a very long and flat river in its upper flow before it gets to the dam.

There is a [gauge on the river Caldo](http://saih.chminosil.es/index.php?url=/datos/ficha/estacion:N019/area:HID) which is very close but the source of this river is in completely different location.

The river should have at least 2 cumecs. Otherwise the landings are too hard and not fun.

**The run**

The first 6-meters drop is very nice but don''t boof it too flat. Then there are two relatively easy slides. After that get out on the left and scout the combination of a big slide and the main 13 meters waterfall. They are both very fun to run but both of the landings are quite hard.

**Access**

_Put in:_ Park at the marked path to the waterfall. This path goes down to the foot bridge, crosses the river and then follows the right bank. Just 100 meters before getting to this bridge turn left to the bushes and go down to the river just above the clean 6 meters drop. It''s a 20 minutes hike from the parking.

_Take out_: Get out on the left at the end of the pool after the big waterfall. Hike up to A Cela village for 20 minutes following a good path.

