**Water**

You can get an idea at the bridge of OU-1206. The rapid upstream should be fun to paddle. The river should have 5-15 cumecs but it''s definitely paddleable with much more.

The [nearest online gauge](http://saih.chminosil.es/index.php?url=/datos/ficha/estacion:N019/area:HID) is on the river Caldo. But Caldo gains and looses water much faster than Caboleiro. Also keep in mind that Caboleiro is born in high mountains and it might snow there. If Caldo has more than 7 cumecs or had it few hours ago then probably it rained enough to make Caboleiro runnable.

