In 300 meters after the crux the canyon opens up and there is a place to sleep on the right.

After another easier box canyon and a steep easy portageable rapid Muksu narrows again into the next box canyon with another class V must run. If the water level is not too high you can scout, portage or chicken-line it on the left once you are already in the canyon. But remember that the rapids change so... improvisation

After you are done with this rapid you can relax a bit. There is still plenty of class V follows but everything is easy to scout and to portage.

Once you are in a red canyon it''s the end of the hard part of the run. From here you will have around 1.5 hours of class III-IV paddling and then 1-2 hours of class II.

Tip 1. Take a strong boat! And a repair kit

Tip 2. Take enough gear to be able to sleep at -10 at least

Tip 3. Bring more gas than your driver believes he needs!

Tip 4. There is no wood at the put in and 15 kilometers downstream

Tip 5. Be ready for high altitude sickness and diarea

Tip 6. The rapids tend to change a lot! It doesn''t make any sense to make more detailed descriptions of the canyons and the must-runs

