## === English ====

Obihingou is a Pamirit''sssics. It''s a really big volume river with enough gradient and easy access. It''s a pure paradise for any big volume fan! The hardest rapids are possible to scout and to portage. Some rapids are not easy to scout.

**Water level**

It''s a glacier river and many people come here in October to get low flows. But even in September the river is not extremely difficult and can be paddled with fun.

**The run**

The lower canyon impresses anyone with it''s beauty and power straight from the beginning.

At high summer flows there are not many eddies and you have to be extremely careful to be always able to catch one.

The first hard rapid is in a narrow limestone canyon and it''s visible from far enough. Scout from the right. The next rapid is hard to scout if you paddle the main one but it''s way easier.

The hardest rapid of the section is known as T-34. It''s a limestone bedrock drop with a huge towback. It''s easy to scout and to portage on the left.

There are still quite a lot of class IV+ - V- rapids downstream. It''s not always easy to stop before them but they are all kind of fair.

After the canyon opens up there is around 15 minutes of class II to the take out. It''s possible to paddle further to a bridge or to the confluence.

