In case you decided to paddle it you can use the following description or the one from the paper guidebook which is quite precise.

**The run** will take you around 2 days

After some flat water paddling the first rapids begin. The rapids are not clean and they are full of siphons and some of them might require portaging.

Then the river becomes more flat for a bit. In 16 km after the put in you will see some buildings on the left and it marks the start of the steepest crux part of the run.

My English is not good enough to describe the following 2 km of the run but I would use all the words I know like manky, nasty, shity e.t.c.

It starts from a big portage (potentially runnable at low flows but it can change). Start portaging on the right bank in advance following a jungle path. It will takeup to 1 hour if you find the way and 2 if not.

