The only highlight is a big steep clean slide.

Towards the end there is a huge spectacular slide-to-waterfall. Take a tiny path in the forest on the right to portage it. There are still some nasty rapids ahead but not too many. The river starts to become cleaner soon.

The only really quality whitewater starts just before the confluence with the left tributary called Riwang and goes on for few kilometers after.

**Access:** _The put in_ quite easy if you use a smartphone with satellite images in it. Its a steep 4x4 drive down followed by a 5 minutes hike to the coordinates suggested here. Alternatively you can park on the main road a 700m before and take a 15 hike down to the river followed by a soon siphon on the river.

Dont _take out_ at the end of this section but keep on paddling the very nice class IV section.

