**Water level**

There is a [gauge](http://www2.meteogalicia.gal/servizos/AugasdeGalicia/estacions.asp?request_locale=es) on this river but we don''t know exactly the references and also the gauge is reported to work bad. The traditional way to check the water level here was to count the steps at the bottom of the put in bridge on the left. If you can see 8 steps then it''s a good water level. 6-7 is high.

**The run**

After 1 kilometer of flat paddling you reach a dam. Portage it on the left. Just after the dam the continuous rapids begin. You can scout them from a water channel on the left. These rapids give you an idea of what follows.

The next portage is in 1.5 kilometers. It''s a 7 meter nasty drop which is best to portage on the left. The next drop is nice and it has a huge pool after. After a short easier section there is another crux. It starts with a tricky and dangerous drop followed by a 45 meters high unrunnable waterfall.

To perform the portage you to climb up the left bank to a small rocky edge. The view from here is impressive. The portage is not that easy. You will have to lower down the boats using ropes.

After the portage there are just isolated easier rapids and a runnable weir. Don''t reduce your attention paddling this section because there are still some surprises!

