**Water level**

The gauge is far downstream after all the dams. It is believed that if the gauge shows 100 cumecs or more then there is enough water. You can check it at the take out. The steepest rapids are just at the take out. With around 30-60 cumecs at the take out the run becomes quite emotional with not many eddies.

The put in is not a good place to check the water level because there is a water release and a dam downstream.

**The run**

After a short warm up there is a lake followed by a dam. Luckily this dam is runnable although it''s quite high. This dam is clean and fun! You can scout it from the right and only here you will really understand how much water is left for the section. If there is less than 40 cumecs everything is easy to scout and to portage. With more water some eddies for scouting become tricky. The combination of two steep rapids just before the take out is a nightmare to portage at high water levels. Luckily it''s good to go even with around 50 cumecs.

