**Water levels**

There is an online gauge. The other way to check the water level is a pillar at the take out bridge. On the upper side there is kind of a shoe. If the water is at the level of the base of the shoe then there is just enough water to paddle. If the water is at the level of its upper part then it''s the optimal flow.

**The run**

The difficulties start in a canyon just after you portage the Xerdiz dam on the left. At higher flows the rapids become very continuous. Some rapids require scouting. Beware of trees especially in the last part of the run and do scout if there is any hesitation. Some lines might be tricky because of trees.

