**The run**

The first 4 kilometers are calm. At the end of this flat section there is an amazing waterfall falling down from the left. As soon as you are finished taking photos of the waterfall there is a nice small slide followed by a rapid with a small boof. Just after this short warm up section there is the crux rapid called "La Hucha". There are different lines at different flows. It''s one of the rapids you don''t want to be mistaken with the line! Portage is on the right.

The next remarkable obstacle is a long slide followed by a rapid with a tricky line which is better to scout. One more slide and couple kilometers with easier whitewater bring us to the take out.

