Start early and save energy for the end, you will notice 3 main pinch points. The first is a sweet and short box canyon that tells you about the character of the run downstream. By mid day you may reach the 2nd Gorge called Gnarnia, you wont be able to see the bottom of the first drop and is a most run. Stay away from the bottom right cave, is not too bad but is not pretty. It has a couple stout drops down from here before it open up again until the walls start getting tighter and deeper when you are into the 3rd gorge that keeps you locked in for the last 10km of the run until the XL portage at the end of the Canyon. Couple good drops guard the exit of the canyon but you can see the light at the end of the tunnel from here where you will find the Rio Dorado coming in from the right. Sleep high since this two rivers can blow up overnight and get to the top of the sandy beaches. Great camping spots along the river from here down.

**Water Level:** There is a gage at the put in next to the village of La Sofia , generally the Cofanes will be IN during a couple weeks of no rain on the whole region. The best way to confirm the level is contacting Daniel Rayo Murillo on facebook messenger and ask him how does it look. He will tell you is good or not. Is never been too low, at 1 on the gage is really good and not recommended to put in above 3.

**Logistics**: This will be a 3 day venue, take one day to travel to the put in, the village of La Sofia is reached with a shuttle set up from the town of Lumbaqui where you can do your shopping as well, or plan it directly from Baeza. Is a long way to get here and drivers do not want to drive back during the night due to safety reasons so plan on starting early. If you contact Daniel ahead of time you can arrange to have a hot dinner cooked for that night and you can also count on having the community house available to sleep the first night. Is recommended to stay at la Sofia the first night so you can put in and know what level you will be running it at.

If everything goes well you should expect to be taking out on the rocky beach of Puerto Nuevo @noon on the 3rd day.

