**The run**

It starts at the confluence with the Strubbach/Loferbach. The beginning is a Slalom race course and is perfect for warm up. After a 90 turn of the river you will see the wooden bridge that marks the beginning of the harder part. Around 100 m after the bridge you should scout the first rapid. On river left there is a trail next to the river so it is easy to portage. Afterwards there are several different lines, boofs and nice eddies.

At the end of the run there is a syphon on river left, make sure to scout or go the chicken line to the right.

