**Water level**

It''s a good idea to paddle this section couple days after a rainfall. It has to look like a normal water level. It should be around 3-7 cumecs at the put in.

**The run**

If you made your way down to the river at the right place you will start with a clean slide combo followed by a nice technical rapid. Some world class class IV+ whitewater on granite rock will bring you to the confluence with Arado. This is the place to be and take pictures!

Meanwhile the river goes on with class IV+ rapids until you reach a big unrunnable section. Portage it on the right with some effort

The rapids after the portage are harder and more dangerous. Proceed with caution, scout the waterfall with a tricky landing and a nasty rapid after it.

**Access**

For the **putting it** you will need to find a small dirt road going down steep from the GPS location. Follow it by foot for around 5 minutes.

There are several options for the **take out**. We took out on the right at the beginning of the lake. There is a very good path going uphill and then the dirt road traversing all the way back to the parking of Tahiti falls. It''s possible to drive this dirt road but it''s forbidden. This hike out takes around 30 minutes', '2-3 days after a rainfall', '3-7 cumecs at the put in', '2018-03-24 15:12:51.989766+00', '2018-03-24 15:12:51.989766+00');

